<title>USA: Cellegy in deal with Glaxo.</title>
<headline>Cellegy in deal with Glaxo.</headline>
<dateline>FOSTER CITY, Calif. 1996-10-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cellegy Pharmaceuticals Inc said it signed a letter of intent with Glaxo Wellcome Plc to license Glylorin, Cellegy's treatment for severe dry-skin that is now in Phase III clinical trials.</p>
<p>Under the arrangement, Cellegy would provide Glaxo with an exclusive license of patent rights for Glylorin in &quot;most of the world's major markets,&quot; and Cellegy would receive up to $8.5 million in up-front and milestone payments. It would also receive a royalty on net sales, assuming the successful completion of product development and market launch.</p>
